
A motorist was killed Sunday night when he lost control of his car on a DeKalb County road and struck a tree. Jack Douglas Hunter III, 39, died when his 2000 Acura left the roadway, overturned and struck a tree in the 1800 block of Brockett Road, according to DeKalb police spokesman Cory Hughes. Hunter was alone in the car, and there were no other vehicles involved, Hughes said. 

